## **Upload to Steam Workshop** 

**Cook your content** 

This is the first process that we are hoping we can automate in the future, but what we were unable to find a quick way of doing is to cook your content. This makes your assets ready to be read and managed in pak files and used in the main game. Make sure to cook for Windows as that is the version of the Mod Kit currently available. 

**![][image1]**

**Publish via mod window** 

Once your content is cooked, go into the workshop UI and make sure that all the fields are filled out correctly, when the information looks good, click Publish and you mod will begin to upload to the Steam Workshop

**![][image2]**

## **Importing a mod** 

**Exporting your source content** 

The Modding Window of the ROA2 Modkit allows you to export the contents of your mod with your Workshop upload to allow others to view and use what you create. If you would like to enable this check the **Include Source Content** box at the bottom of the Workshop settings ![][image3]

Note: This will package all contents found under Content/ModContent/\[Your Mod ID\].

### **Importing otherâ€™s mods** 

**To import the source content of a mod that you have downloaded from the Steam Workshop, press the import button** 

**![][image4]**  
This should open a folder picker directly to the ROA2 steam workshop folder. 

From here you just need to select the root folder (folder will be the mod id of the mod) of the mod you want to import. The contents will be copied into your Content/ModContent folder. ![][image5]
